## Bug Fix: Eliminating the Initial Blue Flash
- **Root Cause Identified:** While [useBrandColor.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/hooks/useBrandColor.ts) applied `.theme-green` to the layout over time, the raw `:root` and `.dark` blocks in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) were still defaulting to the original blue `--primary` colors. Changing locales triggered a NextJS structural update, momentarily stripping the JS-applied theme class before [useBrandColor](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/hooks/useBrandColor.ts#9-45)'s `useEffect` could rehydrate it, causing a rapid "flash" back to the un-themed default (`blue`).
- **Resolution:** Modified the base CSS definitions inside `:root` and `.dark` within [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to natively output the **green** values by default. Now, even without a specific `.theme-[color]` utility class applied during initial SSR or transitional mounting phases, the CSS will naturally resolve to green.

## Optimization: Authentication Layout Update
- **Social Login Reordering**: Modified [CardAuth.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx) to position the Social Login buttons (Google/GitHub) at the top of the authentication card, above the standard Email/Password form. This prioritizes faster onboarding flows as the primary choice for users.
- **Card Spacing Adjustments**: Updated the global Semantic CSS (`.ui-card-content` and `.ui-card-footer` in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css)) to use `1rem` padding (`p-4 pt-0`) down from `1.5rem` (`p-6 pt-0`). This ensures all cards have consistent, slightly tighter padding across the UI, while adjusting the inner spacing elements (like the `divider`) to perfectly match the layout hierarchy.

