## Fix: Thematic Input Background Integration
- Discovered that `.ui-input-primary` and standard inputs were previously using `bg-transparent`. When placed inside colored cards (e.g., green `ui-card`), the inputs visually inherited the card's background color, violating the expected input appearance.
- Replaced `bg-transparent` with `bg-background text-foreground` on `.ui-input` and removed transparencies on base inputs so that their backdrop mimics primary themed `outline` buttons. Inputs are now reliably opaque and styled properly across differently colored panels.

