## Feature: Firebase MFA SMS implementation
- **Backend Custom Claims**: Updated the [functions/src/orchestrator/admin.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/admin.ts), [organization.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/organization.ts), and [organizationUser.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/functions/src/orchestrator/organizationUser.ts) backend orchestrators. Whenever custom claims are set or generated, the user's `phoneNumber` (from their Firebase `UserRecord`) is explicitly parsed and injected into the custom `.claims.phoneNumber` property.
- **FormLogin Integration**:
  - Replaced the simple `email/password` submission in [FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx) with a multi-step component that handles MFA challenges (`auth/multi-factor-auth-required`) using Firebase's `PhoneAuthProvider` and `RecaptchaVerifier`.
  - Added a Forced Enrollment path. If a user logs in successfully via email/password but hasn't yet enrolled any multi-factor mechanism (`multiFactor(user).enrolledFactors.length === 0`), the UI freezes the progression and prompts the user to enroll a phone number via SMS before creating the server-side Next.js session block.
  - Successfully mapped missing localized translation keys (e.g. `mfaVerifyMessage`, `phoneNumberLabel`) across all translation arrays ([en.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/en.json), [it.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/it.json), [es.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/es.json), [fr.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/fr.json), [de.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/de.json), [us.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/us.json)) programmatically.
- **Verification**:
  - `npm run build` returned a successful completion with zero ESLint errors and zero TypeScript compile errors.
  - `functions: tsc` returned a successful compilation output.

## Feature Update: Registration Redirect to MFA Login
- **[FormRegister.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormRegister.tsx) Refactoring**: Removed the [handleLoginSuccess](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx#76-138) function from the registration form. Now, whether a user registers via Email, Google, or Github, they are automatically logged out of the client Firebase session and redirected to `/auth/login?registered=true`.
- **[FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx) Banner**: Intercepts the `registered=true` query parameter and displays a success banner (`layout-auth-error` style with semantic green coloring) prompting the user to log in again. This elegantly forces all newly registered users into the exact same SMS MFA Enrollment loop that existing users follow without duplicating `RecaptchaVerifier` logic.
- **Translations Injected**: The key `"registrationSuccess"` has been seamlessly added into all locale map JSON files in `messages/`.

## Optimization: Social Login MFA Exemption
- **Bypassed Forced SMS Enrollment**: Logic in [FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx) ([handleLoginSuccess](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx#76-138)) has been refined to inspect `user.providerData`. If the user is logging in exclusively via a social provider (`google.com` or `github.com`), the application will no longer forcefully halt the login process to demand an SMS enrollment. Since Google and GitHub inherently manage their own rigorous security and 2FA protocols, this reduces friction while maintaining security for traditional Email/Password users.

## Optimization: FormRegister UI
- **Terms & Privacy Checkbox Relocation**: Moved the terms and privacy acceptance checkbox to the very beginning of the registration form, enforcing its visibility as the primary actionable item.
- **New Authentication Dividers**: Added two new `<CardDivider>` elements to visually separate the form's logical steps.
  - Added `Register.termsDivider` ("Prima cosa: Accetta Privacy & Condizioni") above the checkbox.
  - Added `Register.registerDivider` ("Completa la registrazione") just before the final submission button.
- **Styling Unification**: Modified the main submit button in [FormRegister.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormRegister.tsx) to use the `variant="outline"` property. This aligns it with the thematic styling of [FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx), ensuring a consistent, themed visual hierarchy across the entire authentication flow.
- **Validation**: Conducted a full typescript check via `npm run build` which compiled cleanly with zero errors in 18 seconds.
- **CardAuthSocials Detachment**: Safely extracted the Google and GitHub authentication buttons from the core [CardAuth.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx) component into a newly isolated `CardAuthSocials.tsx` component. This enabled injecting the social buttons directly into [FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx) and [FormRegister.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormRegister.tsx) exactly where desired—specifically placing them *after* the mandatory Privacy & Terms Checkbox on the registration flow.
- **Social Login Suggestion**: Reorganized the layout within `CardAuthSocials.tsx` so that a dividing line and message appear *before* the Google and GitHub login options, correctly encouraging users to use social logins. Programmatically added the new `"socialDivider"` copy across all active languages ([it.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/it.json), [en.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/en.json), [es.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/es.json), [us.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/us.json), [fr.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/fr.json), [de.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/messages/de.json)).
